{"ts":"2026-06-23T19:52:13.077Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-2p38"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Modular declarative authoring: mergeExtensionBlueprints + composeExtensionPackage"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Complete the declarative extension-authoring loop with two missing assembly verbs. Today an author can describe an extension as one ExtensionBlueprint and turn it into a module (composeExtension) and synthesize its manifest (synthesizeExtensionManifest) — but (1) there is no way to build a blueprint MODULARLY across files (a commands module + a search module + a hooks module) and combine them, and (2) there is no single call that returns the whole shippable package (runtime module + on-disk manifest) from one declarative spec. Add mergeExtensionBlueprints(...blueprints) (pure, deterministic modular composition) and composeExtensionPackage(blueprint, identity) (author-once capstone returning { module, manifest } with the synthesized manifest set as the module's authoritative mirror so the two halves never drift). Author once, modularly; ship both halves in one call."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:extensions","area:sdk","authoring","dx"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-23T19:52:13.077Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-23T19:52:13.077Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"7def34500516d4eb0ea8bd00f615e097e8b0af6cf9284d2cb8dee75ca4ace477","message":""}
